stylometry: This value shows the % of the dependant variable determined by the independant variables. Imagine that the demand is the independant variable and price is the independant variable. 80% coefficient of determination would say that 80% of the demand is determined by the price of the product. That leaves 20% of the demand to be determined by unknown variables. Keeping this coefficient high is important because if it is not, then the independant variables used in the regression model are weak and not really contributing to the dependant variable or the model as a whole.
